The Viaduct - the best bars and restaurants in the city! The New Zealand Maritime Museum is here, as well as Silo Park where you can watch outdoor films for free in the evening. You can also catch ferries from here to the amazing islands in the Hauraki Gulf like Waiheke, Tiritiri Matangi, and Rangitoto, as well as go on a whale and dolphin safari.

Federal Street - next to the Sky Tower (you can't miss it!) There are a lot of really nice bars and restaurants and cafes in this street, as well as the Sky City Casino and of course the Sky Tower. Dine at the top of tower at restaurant with the best views in Auckland, and jump off the Sky Walk to get down

host_about:
Hi! My name is Stefan and I live in Auckland city, New Zealand. My favourite thing about living here is that Auckland is a vibrant and buzzing city, but that it also has beautiful beaches and forests on its doorstep when I want a break from the city life.

description:
This is a building with a rich history, unique architecture and superb interiors in each of the two apartments. Walking distance to shops. You will enjoy the comfort and luxury of this space and experience a truly unique accommodation experience.
Whether you are here to ski, hunt, fish or sightsee we are the ideal location to spend a few days and base your day trips from and offer fantastic value and luxury for money.
neighborhood_overview: If you like to walk, or jog you will enjoy the short walk to the Domain -  a huge scenic park with fabulous trees and gardens, bird aviary, bowls club, gym, mini putt golf, skate park, cycle track, tennis courts, playground and an 18 hole golf course open to visitors.
host_about:
I am an active Potter and artist. South Canterbury is home of the famous Temuka Pottery and has some fantastic galleries and artists who are similarly inspired by our magical mountain and coastal scenery. Wine and food lovers can also indulge themselves with a tour of our local restaurants and vineyards. My husband and I share a passion for historic buildings and old things with a story to tell. We can  give you a tour of the building to show you the gallery and mezzanine bar area which has displays of antiques and memorabilia and adjoins the apartments. He is the builder and cabinet maker and I am the designer. We love unique hand crafted historic buildings, furniture, classic cars and art.  South Canterbury has many like minded people that you will meet on your travels. 
When hosting guests and friends, wholesome food and hospitality is how we show our love of people and welcome them to our special place.

name: Hosts on the Coast Cooks Crib
description: Your family will be close to everything when you stay at this centrally located bach. Super close to the beach and Cooks Beach village, and a short drive to Ferry Landing for trip to Whitianga on the passenger ferry. Also a short drive to Hahei or Hot Water Beach.
neighborhood_overview:
Cooks Beach is a popular holiday spot not too far from Whitianga with a stunning white sandy beach and sparkling blue water it's perfect for a morning stroll and swimming. The beach is not patrolled by Surf Lifesavers so always watch the conditions. With Shakespeare Cliff to the west and sheltered Purangi Estuary to the east. Take a walk up Shakespeare Cliff the views are some of the most beautiful you will see. You can also walk down to the beautiful Lonely Bay with its large limestone boulders and white sands, it's a photographer's dream. Cooks Beach itself is perfect for a morning stroll and swimming. You can launch the boat from the Estuary end of the beach, just watch the tides. Cooks Beach has a convenience store and some great eateries. And of course, on the way to Cooks Beach, there are 2 wineries to check out!
Not too far away is Ferry Landing which has Australasia's oldest stone wall wharf built in 1837, from there you can catch the passenger ferry to Whitianga.
